+# Changelog
+
+All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
+
+This file follows the [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/)
+format. Versioning follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).
+
+The authoritative list of what is in v1 versus deferred is
+[`docs/plans/product/V1-SCOPE.md`](docs/plans/product/V1-SCOPE.md).
+
+---
+
+## Versioning
+
+The `etude` binary reports its version via `etude --version`. A plain
+`make build` stamps the binary with `dev`; a release build passes the version
+explicitly (e.g. `make build VERSION=v1.0.0`). See the
+[`## Releasing`](README.md#releasing) section of `README.md` for the full
+mechanics.
+
+---
+
+## [v1.0.0] ‚Äî Unreleased
+
+> v1.0.0 has not been tagged. Cutting the tag is a human release action
+> covered by the v1 release checklist (etude-kb0.4).
+
+### Added
+
+**Commands**
+
+- `etude init` ‚Äî scaffold `.etude/workflow.yaml` and rubric placeholders;
+  register the `refs/etude/*` fetch/push refspec on a git remote.
+- `etude capture` ‚Äî record a stage artifact for the current run.
+- `etude capture-gate` ‚Äî append a structured gate-reviewer record to a run.
+- `etude capture-run` ‚Äî record a complete multi-stage run from a single YAML
+  spec in one operation.
+- `etude run list` / `etude run show` ‚Äî list all stored runs; inspect the
+  detail (including gate records) of one run.
+- `etude sync` ‚Äî push and fetch `refs/etude/*` with a git remote.
+- `etude replay` ‚Äî re-execute a recorded stage end-to-end and emit its output.
+- `etude bench` ‚Äî benchmark a cohort of runs by replaying and judging
+  replay-vs-original; `eval` is available as an internal library consumed by
+  this command (no standalone `etude eval` command in v1).
+- `etude retro capture` / `etude retro generate` / `etude retro list` /
+  `etude retro show` ‚Äî store, generate, list, and inspect retrospectives
+  as `refs/etude/retros/*` refs.
+- `etude gc` ‚Äî report artifact storage and explicitly prune named run refs.
+- `etude reindex` ‚Äî rebuild the derived SQLite query index from run and eval
+  refs.
+- `etude prime` ‚Äî print a structured agent-onboarding primer to stdout (no
+  args, no side effects).
+- `etude log` ‚Äî narrate runs and retros as a chronological timeline
+  (read-only).
+
+**Storage**
+
+- Git-native `refs/etude/*` ref store ‚Äî run records written atomically to
+  per-run refs with no shared write point.
+- Content-addressed inline artifacts ‚Äî blobs stored by hash inside the ref
+  store.
+
+**Run manifests**
+
+- Run manifests v2 and v3 ‚Äî v3 adds gate-reviewer records; the producer
+  record is authoritative.
+- Retro-meta sidecars ‚Äî retrospective metadata stored alongside run records.
+
+---
